Package: splicr
Type: Package
Title: Multiple Argument Piping in R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christopher R. Peterson
Maintainer: Christopher R. Peterson <Christopher.r.peterson@utexas.edu>
Description: The multi-pipe operator (lhs %!>% rhs) passes the elements
    of a list (lhs) into the arguments of a function call (rhs), 
    matching by name and position. This can allow users to chain 
    together functions with multiple inputs and outputs. The multi-pipe
    also enables simple argument splicing for any R function.  
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 2.1.0)
Imports: 
    rlang (>= 0.3.0)
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
